The --keep-until-expiring flag instructs certbot to keep the certificate if it is not near expiry. Usually, this is the right choice, as it prevents multiple restarts to use up your quota.

scp -P 80 /ruta/del/archivo usuario@ip.del.destino:/carpeta/del/destino

cat /sys/class/net/eth0/address
ip link show eth0 
    ip addr show
ip link

config raspberry
network:
    version: 2
    renderer: networkd
    ethernets:
        eth0:
            addresses: [192.168.1.10/24]
            gateway4: 192.168.1.1
            nameservers:
             addresses: [8.8.8.8,4.4.4.2]
            dhcp4: false
            optional: true

Raspberry cambio de ip s estática:
  sudo nano /etc/dhcpcd.conf
  
  interface wlan0
  static ip_address=192.168.x.x/24
  static routers=192.168.x.y
  static domain_name_servers=192.168.x.y 
  where (y = 254 or 1) depends of you gateway

  cat /proc/cpuinfo

  sudo lshw -C CPU
  lscpu
  si salta error al importar #1273 por utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci sustituir por => utf8mb4_unicode_ci

